In what has left many soccer followers curious, PSL Chairman Irvin Khoza and Kaizer Chiefs boss Kaizer Motaung attended the much-awaited EFF Congress on Saturday. They were joined by SAFA Acting CEO Gay Mokoena at the congress that was held in Nasrec in Johannesburg. EFF Commander In Chiefs Julius Malema invited the all powerful soccer
 bosses. Malema acknowledged the trio of Khoza, Motaung and Mokoena when
 he opened his speech. The trio's presence must have left football supporters asking themselves many questions...